tweet: The people of Baltimore are hurting and begging for something to be done. They want to know why this bloodshed keeps happening, what it’s going to take for something to finally change, and they want to know why their legislators have refused to take action.

tweet: I’ve also directed another $35 million to guard against devastating federal cuts and fully fund Victims of Crime Act grants to support victim services providers.

tweet: Additionally, we are investing another $6.5 million to help the Baltimore Police Department expand its Warrant Apprehension Task Force. It is critical that we immediately and aggressively enforce outstanding open warrants to get more violent offenders off the streets.
